 occured in the next fleeting seconds of existance.<br><br>His mind began to fall, to plummet into the depths of itself, searching franticly for the elements that were needed.  Firt it found the center, a place of great power within the mind and begin to call out for the components required for destruction.  The eterial existances of ice, fire and lightening began to swirl around it into a furious funnel of all consuming power.  Now the mind had only one ingrediant left to cause the ultimate destruction, the strength to bind them all together, and compact them in order to collapse them into reality.  This it pooled from its own reserves, stretching and warping itself in an attempt to glean all it could from its own darkened depths.  When finaly enough strength was gathered, it was unleashed on the whirlwind, and as bands of strength began to slither from its core and encase its exterior the fury began to compact, and decrease in size, all the time only growing in power.  As the last band of strength began to exert itself on the whirlwind the portal was opened and the now festering ball of entered existance.<br><br>The mans eyes strained and his body appeared to buckle under the weight.  As his own body seemed to implode in an excruciating drain the world around the mans assailent began to unravel.  The world exploded in a blinding flash of blu and yellow and red, as the flesh of the creature began to bubble, and flow away from the bones it had been intended to encase.  An in an instant of time it was over, a blinding flash and a loud sound were all the evidence that the now slumping grousomly contorted corpse of a creature had met its doom.<br><br>The now drained man sat, and began to rest his mind, for he knew that a similar expendature would soon be required.  And what was all this for, why was this man so drained, and this poor creatures life destroyed?  It was all done for the advancement of his mind and body...something affectionatly refered to as Experie